				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$h$$\end{document}h-day ahead predictive performance (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$h=1,\ldots ,21$$\end{document}h=1,…,21 days) using root mean square errors and mean absolute percentage errors. We also visualized the non-zero parameters in a heatmap to assess the dynamics of potential symptoms of long COVID.

